The Keg is a fairly large chain restaurant but I've only been to the one located in Chandler. It looks like they have locations throughout the US and Canada.  I've been here a couple of times now and have found that the steaks are much better than the prime rib. The last time I went, I had the 20 oz rib eye. It was pretty awesome and cooked perfectly medium-rare. The prime ribs are decent....but pales in comparison to House of Prime Rib in SF.  I recommend getting the baked potato as a side dish and ask for the triple cheese butter. In fact, ask for extra triple cheese butter. It's that good.

