Skip this place.  Unless you get one of the limited couches in the "stadium" area, you'll be stuck with a tiny tv monitor in your booth area.  Food is mediocre. Drinks are okay. Staff is friendly.  They had a $25 per person minimum, but that is not a big deal since its easy to hit that with a few drinks and some food.  Next time I'll just stay in the local sports book area of the hotel I'm staying at.

